ml#_auto._@.Mathlib.Algebra.Field.Defs._hyg.71\">_auto✝</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(nnqsmul : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Rat/Init.html#NNRat\">ℚ≥0</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(nnqsmul_def : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Tactics.html#autoParam\">autoParam</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Rat/Init.html#NNRat\">ℚ≥0</a>) (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">nnqsmul</span> <span class=\"fn\">q</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">q</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span></span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#_auto._@.Mathlib.Algebra.Field.Defs._hyg.110\">_auto✝</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Semifield\">Semifield</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.lean#L174-L174","name":"Semifield","line":174,"kind":"class","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Semifield","doc":"A `Semifield` is a `CommSemiring` with multiplicative inverses for nonzero elements.\n\nAn instance of `Semifield K` includes maps `nnratCast : ℚ≥0 → K` and `nnqsmul : ℚ≥0 → K → K`.\nThose two fields are needed to implement the `DivisionSemiring K → Algebra ℚ≥0 K` instance since we\nneed to control the specific definitions for some special cases of `K` (in particular `K = ℚ≥0`\nitself). See also note [forgetful inheritance].\n\nIf the semifield has positive characteristic `p`, our division by zero convention forces\n`nnratCast (1 / p) = 1 / 0 = 0`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Semifield\"><span class=\"name\">Semifield</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_extends\">extends</span><span class=\"decl_parent\">\n<span class=\"fn\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommSemiring\"><span class=\"name\">CommSemiring</span></a></span></span>\n, <span class=\"decl_parent\">\n<span class=\"fn\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#Inv\"><span class=\"name\">Inv</span></a></span></span>\n, <span class=\"decl_parent\">\n<span class=\"fn\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Div\"><span class=\"name\">Div</span></a></span></span>\n, <span class=\"decl_parent\">\n<span class=\"fn\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Nontrivial/Defs.html#Nontrivial\"><span class=\"name\">Nontrivial</span></a></span></span>\n, <span class=\"decl_parent\">\n<span class=\"fn\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Rat/Init.html#NNRatCast\"><span class=\"name\">NNRatCast</span></a></span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4</div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.lean#L161-L162","name":"DivisionRing.toDivisionSemiring","line":161,"kind":"instance","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.toDivisionSemiring","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.toDivisionSemiring\"><span class=\"name\">DivisionRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">toDivisionSemiring</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing\">DivisionRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionSemiring\">DivisionSemiring</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.lean#L156-L156","name":"DivisionRing.qsmul_def","line":156,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.qsmul_def","doc":"However `qsmul` is defined, it must be propositionally equal to multiplication by `Rat.cast`.\n\nDo not use this lemma directly. Use `Rat.cast_def` instead. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.qsmul_def\"><span class=\"name\">DivisionRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">qsmul_def</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[self : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing\">DivisionRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(a : <a href=\"./Batteries/Data/Rat/Basic.html#Rat\">ℚ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(x : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.qsmul\">DivisionRing.qsmul</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.lean#L152-L152","name":"DivisionRing.qsmul","line":152,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.qsmul","doc":"Scalar multiplication by a rational number.\n\nUnless there is a risk of a `Module ℚ _` instance diamond, write `qsmul := _`. This will set\n`qsmul` to `(Rat.cast · * ·)` thanks to unification in the default proof of `qsmul_def`.\n\nDo not use directly. Instead use the `•` notation. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.qsmul\"><span class=\"name\">DivisionRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">qsmul</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[self : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing\">DivisionRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Data/Rat/Basic.html#Rat\">ℚ</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.lean#L145-L145","name":"DivisionRing.ratCast_def","line":145,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.ratCast_def","doc":"However `Rat.cast q` is defined, it must be propositionally equal to `q.num / q.den`.\n\nDo not use this lemma directly. Use `Rat.cast_def` instead. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.ratCast_def\"><span class=\"name\">DivisionRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">ratCast_def</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[self : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing\">DivisionRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(q : <a href=\"./Batteries/Data/Rat/Basic.html#Rat\">ℚ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">q</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">q</span>.num</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">q</span>.den</span></span></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.lean#L140-L140","name":"DivisionRing.nnqsmul_def","line":140,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.nnqsmul_def","doc":"However `qsmul` is defined, it must be propositionally equal to multiplication by `Rat.cast`.\n\nDo not use this lemma directly. Use `NNRat.smul_def` instead. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.nnqsmul_def\"><span class=\"name\">DivisionRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">nnqsmul_def</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[self : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing\">DivisionRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(q : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Rat/Init.html#NNRat\">ℚ≥0</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(a : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.nnqsmul\">DivisionRing.nnqsmul</a> <span class=\"fn\">q</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">q</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.lean#L136-L136","name":"DivisionRing.nnqsmul","line":136,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.nnqsmul","doc":"Scalar multiplication by a nonnegative rational number.\n\nUnless there is a risk of a `Module ℚ≥0 _` instance diamond, write `nnqsmul := _`. This will set\n`nnqsmul` to `(NNRat.cast · * ·)` thanks to unification in the default proof of `nnqsmul_def`.\n\nDo not use directly. Instead use the `•` notation. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.nnqsmul\"><span class=\"name\">DivisionRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">nnqsmul</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[self : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing\">DivisionRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Rat/Init.html#NNRat\">ℚ≥0</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.lean#L129-L129","name":"DivisionRing.nnratCast_def","line":129,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.nnratCast_def","doc":"However `NNRat.cast` is defined, it must be equal to `a / b`.\n\nDo not use this lemma directly. Use `NNRat.cast_def` instead. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing.nnratCast_def\"><span class=\"name\">DivisionRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">nnratCast_def</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><sp